\begin{document}$$K_{{\text{M,inhibitor}}}  = K_m  \cdot \left( {1 + \frac{{\left[ I \right]}}{{K_I }}} \right)$$\end{document}Where [I] represents the inhibitor concentration, KM,inhibitor the apparent Michaelis constant in presence of the inhibitor and the KI the inhibition constant.
